cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI. 

The paper focuses on visual place recognition for personal localization on a mobile device, which involves computer vision and robotics. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.RO (Robotics) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of state-of-the-art algorithms and modifications to improve processing time and scalability, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves the use of algorithms for recognition and localization, which falls under the scope of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
